definitions.definition: Of or characterized by antiquity ; old-fashioned , quaint , antiquated .
No longer in ordinary use, though still used occasionally to give a sense of antiquity and are still likely to be understood by well-educated speakers and are found in historical texts.

main_definition: Of or characterized by antiquity ; old-fashioned , quaint , antiquated .
secondary_definitions: ( chiefly lexicography , of words ) No longer in ordinary use, though still used occasionally to give a sense of antiquity and are still likely to be understood by well-educated speakers and are found in historical texts.
( archaeology ) Belonging to the archaic period .
